This directory is intentionally empty in source control.

The `cloak-mcp` binary is injected here at .dxt build time by
`scripts/build-dxt.sh <version> <platform-tag> <path-to-cloak-mcp>`,
which stages the contents of `packaging/cloak-dxt/` into a temp dir,
copies the binary to `server/binaries/cloak-mcp`, and zips the result
into `dist/Cloak-<version>-<platform-tag>.dxt`.

The CI `dxt-package` job in `.github/workflows/release.yml` invokes
the same script with a freshly-built per-platform binary. Local
developers can do the same after `cargo build -p cloak-mcp` (or after
building the JS shim under `packages/cloak-mcp/`).

Do NOT commit a binary into this directory.
